  "text": "Why You Can Trust CNET Our expert deal-hunting staff showcases the best price drops and discounts from reputable sellers daily. If you make a purchase using our links, CNET may earn a commission. Cyber Monday may technically be over, but a few good laptop deals are still available for a limited time. Russell Holly is a Managing Editor on the Commerce team at CNET. He works with all of CNET to assemble top recommendations as well as helping everyone find the best way to buy anything at the best price. When not writing for CNET you can find him riding a bike, running around in Jedi robes, or contributing to WOSU public radio's Tech Tuesday segment. Expertise 7 years experience as a smartphone reviewer and analyst, 5 years experience as a competitive cyclist CredentialsAuthor of Taking your Android Tablets to the Max While Cyber Monday has come and gone, you still have one more chance to score amazing savings. If you're in the market for a high-quality laptop that won't break the bank, it's now or never. Several top brands, including Apple, Dell and Lenovo, are offering big discounts on their latest models, though most of the MacBook deals from the holiday weekend have sold out or are now back-ordered. Whether you're after a laptop for work or play, there's a deal waiting for you. But you better act fast if you want to get these prices.Our team of CNET experts has tested all the computers we could get our hands on to help you decide on the best laptop to buy. And we've combed through the bulk of laptop deals to present the top options remaining from reputable retailers like Amazon, Walmart and Best Buy. If you're looking for computing power that's even more mobile, head over to our roundups of the best Cyber Monday phone and tablet deals still live.Best Cyber Monday laptop deals Alienware/CNET This Alienware model is already one of our favorite gaming laptops for folks on a budget, and right now you can pick it up for even less. There are a few different configurations on sale, but this $1,450 model is equipped with an Intel Core Ultra 9 processor, an Nvidia GeForce RTX 4060 GPU, 16GB of RAM and 1TB of storage. This 2024 laptop has a touchscreen display, 16GB of RAM and 512GB of SSD storage. It also has the Snapdragon X Elite processor, AI capabilities through Copilot Plus and gets up to 20 hours of battery life. Best Cyber Monday MacBook deals Apple MacBook Air M1 (13-inch): $599 (save $100). This previous-gen MacBook Air is our top pick for Apple users on a budget.Apple MacBook Pro M4 (14-inch): $1,499 (save $100). Score savings on a cutting-edge Apple laptop that just hit shelves this month.Apple MacBook Pro M4 (16-inch): $2,299 (save $200). Get the biggest current-gen Apple laptop and save $300 on the base M4 Pro model. Other configurations are discounted by up to $400.Best Cyber Monday Chromebook dealsAn excellent affordable Chromebook that comes with 8GB of RAM and 64GB of storage. It has a solid 15.6-inch HD screen and can even be used for some basic gaming along with all of streaming and the standard Chromebook tasks. Lenovo IdeaPad 3i 15.6-inch: $119 (save $130). This model comes with 4GB of RAM and 64GB of memory.Acer Chromebook 315: $139 (save $210). This comes with 4GB of RAM and a solid 128GB memory.Best Cyber Monday gaming laptop deals CNET/ASUS This 16-inch gaming laptop has 16GB of RAM and a GeForce RTX 4060 along with a 1TB SSD. It's not top-end, but it's a very solid choice for pretty much everyone who wants to game on the go and still enjoy solid specs. Lenovo LOQ 15.6\" FHD 144Hz gaming laptop: $600 (save $600). Get half off this laptop now at Walmart.Asus TUF A15 gaming laptop: $943 (save $57). The Asus TUF's processing speed and graphics quality exceed all expectations, allowing it to handle even the most demanding games.Lenovo Legion 7i: $1,500 (save $500). This beast has a 16-inch screen, a 1TB SSD and an RTX 4070. This one's sold out for delivery, but there may be some left for pickup at your local stores.Asus Rog Zephyrus G14: $1,200 (save $400). The 3K visuals on this 14-inch screen look incredible, and it's highly portable.Alienware m16: $1,600 (save $500) . If you want a lot of power, then this 16-inch Alienware model has it, thanks to 32GB of RAM and an RTX 4070.Best Cyber Monday laptop deals for students Acer/CNET This budget-friendly Acer is the best cheap laptop of 2024. With an AMD Ryzen 3 processor, 8GB of RAM and 128GB of storage, it's designed for the basics like scrolling social media and checking your email. It also has a built-in webcam, and an HDMI port and weighs just 3.2 pounds so it's easy to take on the go. Samsung Galaxy Book 4: $530 (save $370). A solid middle-of-the-road option for those who just need the basics.Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon Gen 11: $1,589 (save $1,300). This 14-inch Lenovo is our favorite business laptop of 2024.Microsoft Surface Laptop 7: $899 (save $301). Powerful hardware and a lightweight design earned this Microsoft model a spot on our list of the best laptops of 2024. Amazon says it's temporarily out of stock, but you can still purchase one and wait for a delivery date.What should you look for in a Cyber Monday laptop deal? One of the biggest considerations is which laptop configuration is on sale. With the best laptop deals, typically only a specific version of the laptop is discounted, and making any changes to the hardware, specs or even color could affect the price. This means that sometimes you find that, for example, a model with 512GB of storage is actually cheaper than the 256GB option. Be careful when you're adjusting specs, and look out for sudden price changes. Ultimately, you're looking for the biggest savings compared with not only the price but the usual \"street\" price for a laptop. Don't be fooled by list prices. Use price comparison sites or shopping extensions to make sure the discounted price is actually a good deal.  Which retailers usually offer the best Cyber Monday laptop deals? You can usually find laptop deals at a variety of retailers. Major retailers like Best Buy and Amazon, plus smaller competitors like Newegg, Adorama and B\u0026H Photo, tend to offer sales on more specific models, while manufacturers such as HP, Lenovo and Dell usually host larger sales that cover more models and configurations. If you're looking for a specific model, you'll want to keep checking back throughout the holiday shopping season for the latest batch of deals. Top Cyber Monday deals, according to CNET readers",
